title: Greenwood High School (Texas)
text:
Greenwood High School is a public, co-educational 9-12 secondary school in <a href="Midland%2C%20Texas">Midland, Texas</a>. It is a part of the <a href="Greenwood%20Independent%20School%20District">Greenwood Independent School District</a>.
Demographics.
The demographic breakdown of the 527 students enrolled in 2013-14 was:
21.6% of the students were eligible for free or reduced lunch.
Athletics.
Greenwood High School fields teams in <a href="American%20football">football</a>, <a href="baseball">baseball</a>, <a href="basketball">basketball</a>, <a href="volleyball">volleyball</a>, <a href="cross%20country%20running">cross country</a>, <a href="tennis">tennis</a>, <a href="golf">golf</a>, <a href="softball">softball</a>, <a href="powerlifting">powerlifting</a>, and <a href="track%20and%20field">track and field</a> . They compete in <a href="University%20Interscholastic%20League">UIL</a> district 4A.
Mascot.
The mascot for Greenwood High is the Ranger man. He is commonly seen with 2 <a href="revolvers">revolvers</a> and a <a href="cowboy%20hat">cowboy hat</a>. Recently, a female counterpart has been with the Ranger man named the Rangerette.
Welding.
GISD has had a very impressive <a href="welding">welding</a> team for quite a long time. The leader of the team is the welding instructure, Terryel Gloden.
